<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="38" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="37">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="38" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">
Size 7.2-8.5 mm. 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Agrilus alesi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alesi">Agrilus alesi</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from closely related 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Agrilus auriventris" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auriventris">Agrilus auriventris</taxonomicName>
by the smaller size; by the more transverse pronotum with the maximum 
<pageBreakToken pageId="3" pageNumber="38" start="start">width</pageBreakToken>
in the middle; by the obvious anterior pronotal lobe and by the pygidium with the long spine on apical margin (Fig. 41). See also Appendix.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
